Subject: [PATCH] media: uapi: Add generic serial metadata mbus formats
Git-commit: f28bdda2f87aa0c299ad3ddef3e1fa5134ae8e47
References: jsc#PED-10837
Patch-mainline: v6.10-rc1

Add generic serial metadata mbus formats. These formats describe data
width and packing but not the content itself. The reason for specifying
such formats is that the formats as such are fairly device specific but
they are still handled by CSI-2 receiver drivers that should not be aware
of device specific formats. What makes generic metadata formats possible
is that these formats are parsed by software only, after capturing the
data to system memory.

Also add a definition for "Data Unit" to cover what is essentially a pixel
but is not image data.

